    "note": "frafall doc reports 'address=0x7C87, command=0x6B94'. The library decodes this as command=0x94 (the data byte) because NEC's command field is 8 bits; the 0x6B is the bitwise inverse used as a checksum (0x94 ^ 0x6B == 0xFF). Phase B builds NECCommand(address=0x7C87, command=0x94) and emits canonical timings, which is bit-for-bit what ESPHome's transmit_nec(address=0x7C87, command=0x6B94) produces -- because that ESPHome service also treats the 16-bit command as packed (cmd<<8 | ~cmd)."
